Is it possible to change it?</description><pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2014 14:17:05 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3284/how-to-change-the-color-of-the-mode-indicator/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by joepd for &lt;p&gt;In resizing mode the default background color on the status bar while resizing is red. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is it possible to change it?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3284/how-to-change-the-color-of-the-mode-indicator/?answer=3285#post-id-3285</link><description>The [colors paragraph of the i3bar section of the user guide](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_colors) reads: 

&gt; urgent_workspace
&gt; 
&gt; Border, background
&gt; and text color for a workspace button
&gt; when the workspace contains a window
&gt; with the urgency hint set. **Also
&gt; applies to mode indicators.**

</description><pubDate>Sun, 19 Jan 2014 18:23:23 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/3284/how-to-change-the-color-of-the-mode-indicator/?answer=3285#post-id-3285</guid></item><item><title>Comment by phairland for &lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_colors"&gt;colors paragraph of the i3bar section of the user guide&lt;/a&gt; reads: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;urgent_workspace&lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;p&gt;Border, background
  and text color for a workspace button
  when the workspace contains a window
  with the urgency hint set. &lt;strong&gt;Also
  applies to mode indicators.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
